President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Cherith Norman Chalet as the Representative of the United States of America to the United Nations (U.N.) for U.N. Management and Reform. She will also serve as an Alternate Representative of the United States of America to the Sessions of the General Assembly of the United Nations. Chalet has been serving as the U.N. Management and Reform Counselor for the United States Mission to the U.N. since 2014. 

Trump also intends to nominate Michael R. Bright as the President of the Government National Mortgage Association, Department of Housing and Urban Development. Bright is currently the Executive Vice President, Chief Operating Officer, and Acting President of the Government National Mortgage Association.

In addition, President Trump intends to appoint Gary L. Bauer, Nadine Maenza, and Johnnie Moore as Members of the United States Commission on International Religious Freedom.